Description: Oval handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine mid red-brown; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31, 40). Name Polyaratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0198.14.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1137)
